libtmx
------------------------------------------
libtmx is a C++11 library for reading TMX files. TMX is a XML dialect used in
Tiled, a tile map editor.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.1-1
  libboost_filesystem1.66-1.66.0-1
  libboost_system1.66-1.66.0-1
  libgcc1-12.4.0-3
  libstdc++6-12.4.0-3
  libtinyxml2_6-6.0.0-1
  libtmx0-devel-0.4.0-1bl3
  libtmx0_0-0.4.0-1bl3
  pkg-config-2.4.3-1
  zlib0-1.3.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.44-1
  cmake-3.28.3-1
  cygport-0.36.9-1
  gcc-core-12.4.0-3
  gcc-g++-12.4.0-3
  libboost-devel-1.66.0-1
  libtinyxml2-devel-6.0.0-1
  ninja-1.12.1-1
  zlib-devel-1.3.1-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/jube/libtmx

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/jube/libtmx/archive/refs/tags/v0.4.0.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack libtmx-0.4.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./libtmx-0.4.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libtmx-0.4.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libtmx-0.4.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libtmx0_0-0.4.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libtmx0-devel-0.4.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(libtmx)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/libtmx.README
  /usr/share/doc/libtmx/CONTRIBUTING.md
  /usr/share/doc/libtmx/COPYING
